On Thu, 17 Jan 2002, cmeanley wrote:

> Brian,
> what you have is state minimums 15/30/5 15k per person,30k per accident and
> 5k property damage.Nothing there to protect you or your bus. Best thing to
> do is shop until you find a good price and agent.To raise your liability
> limits to 1mil is fairly cheap, its the comprehensive on your vehicle that
> costs.

how true, in  Maryland I have only found two companies that will put
comprehensive on an old VW daily driver.

Farmers and MetLife.

I had Farmer's and had no problem with em but 
MetLife gave me much better rates for the same coverage so I changed about
2 years ago

This information is only my experience in Baltimore area

Bob


